1
00:00:30,960 --> 00:00:32,560
Aargh!

2
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:39,640
(HE GRUNTS)

3
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:42,360
(BIG BEN STRIKES)

4
00:00:49,080 --> 00:00:51,880
Aaargh!

5
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:04,280
(HE SIGHS)

6
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:12,680
YOUNG GIRL: Dear Santa, thank you
for the dolls and pencils and the fish.

7
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:16,280
It's Easter now,
so I hope I didn't wake you.

8
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:19,840
But honest, it is an emergency.

9
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:23,680
There's a crack in my wall.

10
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:30,960
Aunt Sharon says
it's just an ordinary crack, but...

11
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:34,880
I know it's not, because...
at night, there's voices.

12
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:39,280
So please, please,
could you send someone to fix it?

13
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:41,520
Or a policeman. Or...

14
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:46,120
(METALLIC THRUMMING OUTSIDE)

15
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,800
(CRASH!)

16
00:02:53,480 --> 00:02:54,960
Back in a moment.

17
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,280
Thank you, Santa.

18
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:19,800
Can I have an apple?

19
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:23,920
All I can think about - apples.

20
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,600
I love apples.
Maybe I'm having a craving.

21
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,280
That's new -
never had cravings before.

22
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,920
Whoa!

23
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:38,120
Look at that!

24
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,040
Are you OK?

25
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:43,840
Just had a fall. All the way down there,
right to the library.

26
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:45,080
Hell of a climb back up.

27
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,720
- You're soaking wet.
- I was in the swimming pool.

28
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:51,240
- You said you were in the library.
- So was the swimming pool.

29
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:54,760
- Are you a policeman?
- Why?

30
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:57,080
Did you call a policeman?

31
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:59,680
Did you come about
the crack in my wall?

32
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,920
What cra...? Argh!

33
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:06,600
Are you all right, mister?

34
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:09,120
No, I'm fine, it's OK.

35
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:12,600
This is all perfectly norm...

36
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:18,560
Who are you?

37
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:23,120
I don't know yet. I'm still cooking.

38
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:25,440
Does it scare you?

39
00:05:25,520 --> 00:05:27,360
No, it just looks a bit weird.

40
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:29,320
No, no, no. The crack in your wall.

41
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:32,840
- Does it scare you?
- Yes.

42
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,680
Well, then, no time to lose.

43
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:38,040
I'm the Doctor.
Do everything I tell you,

44
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:41,360
don't ask stupid questions
and don't wander off.

45
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:48,360
Are you all right?

46
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:50,720
Early days.

47
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,640
Steering's a bit off.

48
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:03,280
If you're a doctor,
why does your box say Police?

49
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,760
(HE COUGHS)
That's disgusting. What is that?

50
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,880
- An apple.
- Apples are rubbish. I hate apples.

51
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,320
You said you loved them.

52
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:20,400
No, no, I love yoghurt. Yoghurt's
my favourite. Give me yoghurt.

53
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,440
I hate yoghurt,
it's just stuff with bits in.

54
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:37,480
- You said it was your favourite.
- New mouth, new rules.

55
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:42,360
It's like eating after cleaning your
teeth, everything tastes...wro-agh!

56
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,560
What is it? What's wrong with you?

57
00:06:44,640 --> 00:06:47,120
Wrong with me? It's not my fault.

58
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:49,840
Why can't you give me decent food?
You're Scottish - fry something.

59
00:06:53,840 --> 00:06:55,880
Ah! Bacon!

60
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:03,840
Bacon.

61
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:05,480
That's bacon.

62
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:08,120
Are you trying to poison me?

63
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:15,400
Ah. You see? Beans.

64
00:07:18,320 --> 00:07:21,520
Beans are evil. Bad, bad beans.

65
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,400
Bread and butter.

66
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,960
Now you're talking.

67
00:07:30,040 --> 00:07:32,520
- (PLATE SMASHES, CAT MIAOWS)
- And stay out!

68
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:39,440
We've got some carrots.

69
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:43,040
Carrots? Are you insane?
No, wait, hang on.

70
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:47,080
I know what I need.
I need...I need...I need...

71
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:49,240
fish fingers and custard.

72
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:07,400
- Funny.
- Am I?

73
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:10,240
Good. Funny's good.

74
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:12,560
- What's your name?
- Amelia Pond.

75
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:14,280
Ah, that's a brilliant name.

76
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:19,120
"Amelia Pond",
like a name in a fairy tale.

77
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,320
Are we in Scotland, Amelia?

78
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,480
No. Had to move to England.

79
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:25,680
It's rubbish.

80
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:29,120
So what about your mum and dad, then?
Are they upstairs?

81
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,880
- Thought we'd have woken them by now.
- I don't have a mum and dad.

82
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,160
Just an aunt.

83
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,920
I don't even have an aunt.

84
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:39,600
You're lucky.

85
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:41,520
I know.

86
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:45,400
So, your aunt.

87
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,680
Where is she?

88
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,360
She's out.

89
00:08:50,360 --> 00:08:51,800
And she left you all alone?

90
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:54,440
- I'm not scared.
- You're not scared of anything!

91
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:58,960
Box falls out of the sky, man falls
out of box, man eats fish custard,

92
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:02,760
and look at you,
just sitting there.

93
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:07,600
- So you know what I think?
- What?

94
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:11,920
Must be a hell of a scary crack
in your wall.

95
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,680
You've had some cowboys in here.

96
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:28,560
Not actual cowboys,

97
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,600
though that can happen.

98
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:35,560
I used to hate apples,
so my mum put faces on them.

99
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:46,480
She sounds good, your mum.
I'll keep it for later.

100
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:52,040
This wall is solid and the crack
doesn't go all the way through it.

101
00:09:53,240 --> 00:09:56,760
So here's a thing -
where's the draught coming from?

102
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:02,800
Wibbly-wobbly, timey-wimey.
You know what the crack is?

103
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,880
What?

104
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:06,120
It's a crack.

105
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:12,760
I'll tell you something funny.
If you knocked this wall down,

106
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:16,040
the crack would stay put,
cos the crack isn't in the wall.

107
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:19,160
- Where is it, then?
- Everywhere.

108
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:22,360
In everything. It's a split
in the skin of the world.

109
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:27,520
Two parts of space and time
that should never have touched,

110
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,400
pressed together...

111
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:34,200
...right here in the wall
of your bedroom.

112
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:36,640
- Sometimes, can you hear...?
- A voice.

113
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,440
Yes.

114
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:40,480
(ECHOING VOICE)

115
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:52,520
Prisoner Zero has escaped.

116
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:55,480
- Prisoner Zero?
- "Prisoner Zero has escaped."”

117
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:57,960
That's what I heard.
What does it mean?

118
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,600
Prisoner Zero has escaped.

119
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:06,720
It means that, on the other side
of this wall, there's a prison

120
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,480
and they've lost a prisoner.
Do you know what that means?

121
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:12,280
- What?
- You need a better wall.

122
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:15,200
The only way to close the breach
is to open it all the way.

123
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,880
The forces will invert
and it'll snap itself shut.

124
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:22,360
- Or...
- What?

125
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:26,120
You know when grown-ups tell you
everything's going to be fine

126
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,920
and you think they're probably lying
to make you feel better?

127
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,120
Yes.

128
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:33,440
Everything's going to be fine.

129
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:55,400
Prisoner Zero has escaped.

130
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,360
Prisoner Zero has escaped.

131
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,360
Hello?

132
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,920
Hello!

133
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:11,440
What's that?

134
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:23,800
There. You see, told you it would close.
Good as new.

135
00:12:23,880 --> 00:12:27,200
What was that thing?
Was that Prisoner Zero?

136
00:12:27,280 --> 00:12:30,120
No. I think that was
Prisoner Zero's guard.

137
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:33,280
Whatever it was, it sent me
a message. Psychic paper -

138
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:35,800
takes a lovely little message.

139
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,440
"Prisoner Zero has escaped.”

140
00:12:38,520 --> 00:12:40,000
But why tell us?

141
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:44,040
Unless...

142
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,320
Unless what?

143
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:49,560
Unless Prisoner Zero
escaped through here.

144
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,840
But he couldn't have.

145
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:53,640
We'd know.

146
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:02,240
It's difficult.
Brand-new me, nothing works yet.

147
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:04,720
But there's something
I'm missing...

148
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,000
...in the corner...

149
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,120
...of my eye.

150
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:21,360
(ECHOED BANGING)

151
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:24,640
No, no, no, no, no, no!

152
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,720
I've got to get back in there.

153
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:31,000
The engines are phasing.
It's going to burn!

154
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,200
But...

155
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,240
...it's just a box!

156
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,560
- How can a box have engines?
- It's not a box.

157
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:40,360
It's a time machine.

158
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:43,400
What, a real one?

159
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,680
You've got a real time machine?

160
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:47,920
Not for much longer
if I can't get her stabilised.

161
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:51,280
Five-minute hop into the future
should do it.

162
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,760
Can I come?

163
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:56,000
Not safe in here, not yet. Five minutes.
Give me five minutes.

164
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,400
I'll be right back.

165
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:01,400
People always say that.

166
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,360
Am I people?

167
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:11,080
Do I even look like people?

168
00:14:11,160 --> 00:14:12,840
Trust me.

169
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,400
I'm the Doctor.

170
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:29,280
Geronimo!

171
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,160
(SPLASH!)

172
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:35,760
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

173
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,760
(CLOCK TICKS)

174
00:16:09,960 --> 00:16:13,360
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

175
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,520
Amelia!

176
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:27,320
Amelia, I worked out what it was.
I know what I was missing!

177
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:29,880
You've got to get out of there!

178
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,840
Amelia?

179
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:38,680
Amelia, are you all right?
Are you there?

180
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:41,400
Prisoner Zero is here.

181
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:44,560
Prisoner Zero is here!
Prisoner Zero is here!

182
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:47,080
Do you understand me?
Prisoner Zero is...

183
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:53,320
(SIREN BLARES)

184
00:17:09,840 --> 00:17:15,000
So...they all called out at once,
that's what you're saying?

185
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:18,160
All of them, all the coma patients.

186
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:21,920
You do understand that these people
are all comatose, don't you?

187
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,440
- They can't speak.
- Yes, Dr Ramsden.

188
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:27,520
Then why are you wasting my time?

189
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:31,400
- Because they called for you.
- Me?

190
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,720
MAN: Doctor.

191
00:17:39,520 --> 00:17:40,680
Doctor.

192
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:44,000
Doctor.

193
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:48,160
Doctor. Doctor...

194
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:51,040
ALL PATIENTS: Doctor... Doctor...

195
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:55,080
Doctor... Doctor...

196
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:58,880
VOICES ECHO: Doctor...!

197
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:04,360
White male, mid-20s,
breaking and entering.

198
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:06,760
Send me some back-up,
I've got him restrained.

199
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:11,440
Oi, you! Sit still.

200
00:18:13,320 --> 00:18:16,520
Cricket bat.
I'm getting cricket bat.

201
00:18:16,600 --> 00:18:18,440
You were breaking and entering.

202
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:21,960
That's much better.

203
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:25,040
Brand-new me, whack on the head.
Just what it needed.

204
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,760
Do you want to shut up now?
I've got back-up on the way.

205
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:30,080
Hang on, wait -
you're a policewoman.

206
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:32,600
You're breaking and entering.
See how this works?

207
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,520
What are you doing here?
Where's Amelia?

208
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:35,600
Amelia Pond?

209
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:38,720
Yeah. Amelia. Little Scottish girl.
Where is she?

210
00:18:38,800 --> 00:18:41,480
I promised her five minutes
but the engines were phasing.

211
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:46,280
I suppose I must have gone a bit far.
Has something happened to her?

212
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:50,080
Amelia Pond hasn't lived here
in a long time.

213
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,520
How long?

214
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:57,880
- Six months.
- No!

215
00:18:57,960 --> 00:19:02,000
No, no, no!
I can't be six months late!

216
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:03,800
I said five minutes. I promised.

217
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:09,640
What happened to her?
What happened to Amelia Pond?

218
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,080
Sarge, it's me again. Hurry it up.

219
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:15,280
This guy knows something
about Amelia Pond.

220
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,240
I don't think they were even conscious.

221
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:34,440
Dr Ramsden, there is another
sort of, um...funny thing.

222
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:37,440
Yes, I know. Dr Carver told me
about your conversation.

223
00:19:37,560 --> 00:19:41,880
We've been very patient with you, Rory.
You're a good nurse, but for God's sake!

224
00:19:41,960 --> 00:19:43,400
I've seen them.

225
00:19:43,480 --> 00:19:46,720
These patients are under
24-hour supervision!

226
00:19:46,800 --> 00:19:48,560
We know if their blood pressure changes.

227
00:19:48,640 --> 00:19:50,120
There's no possibility
you'd have seen them

228
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,440
wandering in the village!
Why are you giving me your phone?!

229
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,560
It's a camera too.

230
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:59,120
(PAGER BEEPS)

231
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:03,560
You need to take some time off, Rory.
A lot of time off.

232
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,280
Start now.

233
00:20:05,360 --> 00:20:06,640
Now!

234
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,440
I need to speak to whoever lives
in this house right now.

235
00:20:15,520 --> 00:20:18,240
- I live here.
- But you're the police.

236
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,520
And this is where I live!
You got a problem with that?

237
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,360
How many rooms?

238
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:25,480
- I'm sorry, what?
- On this floor.

239
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,800
How many rooms on this floor?
Count them.

240
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:27,920
Why?

241
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,840
Because it will change your life.

242
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,000
Five.

243
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:36,160
- One, two, three, four, five.
- Six.

244
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:38,960
- Six?
- Look.

245
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,440
- Look where?
- Exactly where you never want to look.

246
00:20:41,520 --> 00:20:43,840
The corner of your eye. Look behind you.

247
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:59,120
That's... That is not possible.

248
00:20:59,200 --> 00:21:00,760
How's that possible?

249
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:04,400
There's a perception filter all round
the door. Sensed it last time I was here.

250
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,600
Should've seen it.

251
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:09,720
But that's a whole room. That's
a whole room I've never even noticed.

252
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:12,880
The filter stops you noticing.
Something came here a while ago to hide.

253
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:15,920
It's still hiding
and you need to uncuff me now!

254
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:21,240
- I don't have the key. I lost it.
- How can you have lost it?!

255
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,680
Stay away from that door!

256
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:28,160
Do not touch that door!

257
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:30,720
Listen to me! Do not open that...

258
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:33,400
Why does no-one ever listen to me?

259
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:36,120
Do I just have a face
that nobody listens to?

260
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:38,560
Again?

261
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:43,080
My screwdriver, where is it? Silver thing,
blue at the end. Where did it go?

262
00:21:44,280 --> 00:21:47,320
- There's nothing here.
- Whatever's in there stopped you seeing

263
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,240
the whole room -
what makes you think you could see it?

264
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:52,440
Now, please, just get out!

265
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:55,720
- Silver, blue at the end?
- My screwdriver, yeah.

266
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:56,920
It's here.

267
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,960
Must have rolled under the door.

268
00:22:00,320 --> 00:22:03,120
Yeah. Must have.

269
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:13,000
And then it must have jumped up
on the table.

270
00:22:15,480 --> 00:22:17,280
Get out of there.

271
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:21,560
Get out of there!

272
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:26,120
Get out!

273
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,480
Get out of there!

274
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:41,320
What is it? What are you doing?

275
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:43,960
There's nothing here, but...

276
00:22:45,160 --> 00:22:46,400
Corner of your eye.

277
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:50,320
What is it?

278
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:53,760
Don't try to see it. If it knows
you've seen it, it will kill you.

279
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,720
Don't look at it.

280
00:22:55,800 --> 00:22:58,800
Do not...look.

281
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,280
- (SHE SCREAMS)
- Get out!

282
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:04,320
Give me that!

283
00:23:06,840 --> 00:23:08,000
(LATCH CLICKS)

284
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:13,240
Come on. What's the bad alien done to you?

285
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:16,520
- Will that door hold it?
- Oh, yeah, yeah, course!

286
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:19,080
It's an inter-dimensional multi-form
from outer space -

287
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,400
they're all terrified of wood(!)

288
00:23:23,640 --> 00:23:25,880
What's that? What's it doing?

289
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,960
I don't know. Getting dressed?
Run. Just go.

290
00:23:32,040 --> 00:23:34,720
- Your back-up's coming, I'll be fine.
- There is no back-up.

291
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:37,640
- I heard you call for back-up.
- It's a pretend radio.

292
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:41,920
- But you're a policewoman.
- I'm a kissogram!

293
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:53,640
- But it's just...
- No, it isn't.

294
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:55,960
Look at the faces.

295
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:58,160
(GROWLING)

296
00:24:00,520 --> 00:24:02,720
(HE BARKS)

297
00:24:02,800 --> 00:24:06,360
What? I'm sorry, but what?!

298
00:24:06,440 --> 00:24:08,600
It's all one creature.
One creature disguised as two.

299
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:11,680
Clever old multi-form.

300
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:15,520
A bit of a rush job, though.
Got the voice a bit muddled, did you?

301
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:19,040
Mind you, where did you get
the pattern from?

302
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:22,000
You'd need a psychic link, a live feed.
How did you fix that?

303
00:24:22,080 --> 00:24:24,840
(SNARLS LIKE DOG)

304
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:27,960
(SNARLING ECHOES)

305
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:42,480
(SNARLS NOT LIKE DOG)

306
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:44,960
Stay, boy!

307
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:50,920
Her and me, we're safe.
Want to know why? She sent for back-up.

308
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,520
I didn't send for back-up!

309
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:56,440
I know. That was a clever lie to save
our lives. OK, yeah, no back-up!

310
00:24:56,520 --> 00:24:58,600
That's why we're safe.
Alone, we're not a threat to you.

311
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:02,280
If we had back-up,
then you'd have to kill us!

312
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:05,640
VOICE: Attention, Prisoner Zero.
The human residence is surrounded.

313
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:08,760
- Attention Prisoner Zero...
- What's that?

314
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,640
- ...the human residence is surrounded.
- That would be back-up. OK,

315
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:14,480
one more time. We do have back-up
and that's definitely why we're safe.

316
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:16,080
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

317
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:18,640
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

318
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:22,240
Safe apart from,
you know, incineration.

319
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,640
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

320
00:25:25,720 --> 00:25:28,480
- or the human residence will be...
- Wait, come on.

321
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:31,880
Prisoner Zero will vacate the human
residence, or the human residence

322
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:33,600
will be incinerated.

323
00:25:33,680 --> 00:25:37,120
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

324
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,400
- or the human residence will be...
- Run!

325
00:25:45,920 --> 00:25:49,280
...the human residence, or the human
residence will be incinerated.

326
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:51,040
- Kissogram?
- Yes, a kissogram!

327
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:52,840
Why do you pretend
to be a policewoman?

328
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,880
You broke into my house!
It was this or a French maid!

329
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:57,640
What's going on? Tell me!

330
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:00,240
Tell me!

331
00:26:00,280 --> 00:26:03,640
An alien convict is hiding in your spare
room disguised as a man and a dog,

332
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:06,400
and some other aliens are about to
incinerate your house. Any questions?

333
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:07,520
- Yes.
- Me, too.

334
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:12,560
No, no, no! Don't do that, not now!
It's still rebuilding, not letting us in!

335
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:15,560
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence...

336
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:16,960
Come on!

337
00:26:17,040 --> 00:26:20,960
No, wait, hang on, hang on,
wait, wait, wait. The shed.

338
00:26:21,040 --> 00:26:23,920
I destroyed that shed last time
I was here, smashed it to pieces.

339
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:26,560
- So there's a new one. Let's go.
- But the new one's got old.

340
00:26:26,640 --> 00:26:28,840
It's ten years old at least.

341
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:32,120
12 years. I'm not six months late,
I'm 12 years late.

342
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,760
- He's coming.
- You said six months.

343
00:26:33,840 --> 00:26:35,520
- Why did you say six months?
- We've got to go.

344
00:26:35,600 --> 00:26:39,160
This matters. This is important.
Why did you say six months?

345
00:26:39,240 --> 00:26:41,680
(SCOTTISH ACCENT) Well,
why did you say five minutes?!

346
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:45,720
- What?
- Come on.

347
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:46,560
What?

348
00:26:46,640 --> 00:26:48,440
- Come on!
- What?

349
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:51,360
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

350
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:54,240
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

351
00:27:00,240 --> 00:27:02,360
- You're Amelia.
- You're late.

352
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:05,440
- Amelia Pond. You're the little girl.
- I'm Amelia and you're late.

353
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:06,520
- What happened?
- 12 years.

354
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:08,680
- You hit me with a cricket bat.
- 12 years.

355
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:11,360
- A cricket bat.
- 12 years and four psychiatrists.

356
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:14,080
- Four?
- I kept biting them.

357
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:16,040
- Why?
- They said you weren't real.

358
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,920
(GARBLED, THROUGH SPEAKER) Prisoner
Zero will vacate the human residence,

359
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:21,520
or the human residence
will be incinerated. Repeat...

360
00:27:21,600 --> 00:27:23,480
No, no, no, come on.

361
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:27,040
What? We're being staked out
by an ice-cream van?

362
00:27:27,120 --> 00:27:30,240
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence...

363
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:32,480
What's that?
Why are you playing that?

364
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,920
It's supposed to be Clair De Lune.

365
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,040
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

366
00:27:36,120 --> 00:27:39,200
or the human residence
will be incinerated. Repeat,

367
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:42,000
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

368
00:27:42,080 --> 00:27:45,320
or the human residence
will be incinerated. Repeat...

369
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:47,680
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence...

370
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:50,880
...or the human residence
will be incinerated.

371
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,840
Doctor, what's happening?

372
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:55,280
(ANNOUNCEMENT CONTINUES)

373
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:05,280
Repeat, Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

374
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,160
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

375
00:28:07,240 --> 00:28:10,520
Repeat, Prisoner Zero
will vacate the human residence,

376
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:13,120
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

377
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,760
Hello! Sorry to burst in,

378
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:21,040
we're doing a special on television
faults in this area. ...Also, crimes.

379
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:25,120
- Let's have a look.
- I was just about to phone.

380
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:27,520
It's on every channel.

381
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:31,080
Hello, Amy, dear.
Are you a policewoman now?

382
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:34,600
- Well, sometimes...
- I thought you were a nurse.

383
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:37,760
I can be a nurse.

384
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:40,960
- Or, actually, a nun?
- I dabble.

385
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:45,920
Amy, who is your friend?

386
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:49,080
- Who's Amy? You were Amelia.
- Yeah, now I'm Amy.

387
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:52,400
Amelia Pond - that was a great name.

388
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:54,800
Bit fairy tale.

389
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:57,600
I know you, don't I?

390
00:28:57,680 --> 00:29:00,520
I've seen you somewhere before.

391
00:29:00,600 --> 00:29:03,520
Not me. Brand-new face...

392
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:06,560
First time on.
And what sort of job's a kissogram?

393
00:29:06,640 --> 00:29:09,600
I go to parties and I kiss people.

394
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:13,720
With outfits. It's a laugh.

395
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:16,280
- You were a little girl five minutes ago.
- You're worse than my aunt.

396
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,600
I'm the Doctor,
I'm worse than everybody's aunt.

397
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:22,840
And that is not
how I'm introducing myself.

398
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:29,840
RADIO: Repetez, le Prisonnier...
...2Zero wird der menschliche...

399
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:33,720
OK, so it's everywhere,
in every language.

400
00:29:33,800 --> 00:29:36,680
They're broadcasting
to the whole world.

401
00:29:40,840 --> 00:29:43,240
AMY: What's up there?
What are you looking for?

402
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:50,840
OK, planet this size, two poles,
your basic molten core...

403
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:53,640
they're going to need
a 40% fission blast.

404
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:56,120
But they'll have to power up first,
won't they?

405
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:59,960
So assuming a medium-sized starship,
that's 20 minutes.

406
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:01,880
What do you think? 20 minutes?

407
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:05,760
Yeah, 20 minutes.

408
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:07,600
We've got 20 minutes.

409
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:10,360
- 20 minutes to what?
- Are you the Doctor?

410
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:15,280
He is, isn't he? He's the Doctor!
The Raggedy Doctor.

411
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:17,480
All those cartoons you did,
when you were little.

412
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:20,560
The Raggedy Doctor - it's him.

413
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:22,320
(WHISPERS) Shut up.

414
00:30:22,400 --> 00:30:24,560
Cartoons?

415
00:30:25,760 --> 00:30:28,160
Gran, it's him, isn't it?

416
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:31,480
- It's really him!
- Jeff, shut up! 20 minutes to what?

417
00:30:31,560 --> 00:30:34,800
TV: ...human residence
will be incinerated. Repeat...

418
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:37,960
The human residence.
They're not talking about your house,

419
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:42,080
they're talking about the planet.
Somewhere up there, there's a spaceship.

420
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:44,320
And it's going to incinerate the planet.

421
00:30:44,400 --> 00:30:49,440
...will be incinerated. Repeat, Prisoner
Zero will vacate the human residence,

422
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:53,560
- or the human residence will be...
- 20 minutes to the end of the world.

423
00:30:54,640 --> 00:30:57,840
...residence will be incinerated.
Repeat,

424
00:30:57,920 --> 00:31:00,480
Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

425
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:02,920
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

426
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,680
Repeat, Prisoner Zero will vacate
the human residence,

427
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:07,880
or the human residence
will be incinerated.

428
00:31:09,840 --> 00:31:12,200
- What is this place? Where am I?
- Leadworth.

429
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:13,960
- Where's the rest of it?
- This is it.

430
00:31:14,040 --> 00:31:15,560
- Is there an airport?
- No.

431
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:16,840
- A nuclear power station?
- No.

432
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:18,280
- Even a little one?
- No.

433
00:31:18,360 --> 00:31:20,200
- Nearest city?
- Gloucester, half an hour by car.

434
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,480
We don't have half an hour.
Do we have a car?

435
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:24,560
- No.
- Well, that's good! Fantastic, that is(!)

436
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:28,080
20 minutes to save the world
and I've got a post office. And it's shut!

437
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,800
What is that?

438
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:32,320
It's a duck pond.

439
00:31:36,720 --> 00:31:39,480
- Why aren't there any ducks?
- I don't know. There's never any ducks.

440
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,400
Then how do you know it's a duck pond?

441
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:43,720
It just is.
Is it important, the duck pond?

442
00:31:43,800 --> 00:31:45,360
I don't know. Why would I know?

443
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:49,960
This is too soon.

444
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:52,480
I'm not ready, I'm not done yet.

445
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,240
What's happening?
Why's it going dark?

446
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,160
- So what's wrong with the sun?
- Nothing.

447
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:13,040
You're looking at it
through a force-field.

448
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:15,160
They've sealed off
your upper atmosphere,

449
00:32:15,240 --> 00:32:16,880
now they're getting ready
to boil the planet.

450
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:21,680
Oh, and here they come -
the human race.

451
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:26,240
The end comes, as it was
always going to - down a video phone!

452
00:32:26,320 --> 00:32:27,960
This isn't real, is it?

453
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,760
- This is some kind of big wind-up.
- Why would I wind you up?

454
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:32,880
- You told me you had a time machine.
- And you believed me.

455
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,440
Then I grew up.

456
00:32:34,520 --> 00:32:37,160
Oh, you never want to do that.
No, hang on, shut up, wait!

457
00:32:37,240 --> 00:32:40,720
I missed it. I saw it
and I missed it. What did I see?

458
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,720
I saw... What did I see?

459
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,000
(RAPID CLICKING)

460
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:16,960
20 minutes.

461
00:33:17,040 --> 00:33:18,480
I can do it.

462
00:33:18,560 --> 00:33:20,120
20 minutes, the planet burns.

463
00:33:20,160 --> 00:33:24,000
Run to your loved ones and say goodbye,
or stay and help me.

464
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:27,560
- No.
- I'm sorry?

465
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:28,880
No!

466
00:33:28,960 --> 00:33:31,200
Amy, no, no, what are you doing?

467
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:36,360
- (LOCK BEEPS)
- Are you out of your mind?

468
00:33:36,440 --> 00:33:38,440
- Who are you?
- You know who I am.

469
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:39,920
No, really, who are you?

470
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:41,160
Look at the sky!
End of the world, 20 minutes.

471
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:44,360
- Better talk quickly, then!
- Amy, I am going to need my car back.

472
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,240
Yes, in a bit.
Now go and have coffee.

473
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,520
Right, yes.

474
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:53,000
Catch.

475
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:59,000
I'm the Doctor.

476
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,760
I'm a time traveller.

477
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:04,320
Everything I told you
12 years ago is true. I'm real.

478
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:07,320
What's happening in the sky is real,
and if you don't let me go now,

479
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:09,800
everything you've ever known is over.

480
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:15,920
- I don't believe you.
- Just 20 minutes.

481
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:19,320
Just believe me for 20 minutes.

482
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:24,120
Look at it.
Fresh as the day you gave it to me.

483
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:25,880
And you know it's the same one.

484
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,520
Amy...

485
00:34:46,600 --> 00:34:49,120
believe for 20 minutes.

486
00:34:57,680 --> 00:34:59,680
- What do we do?
- Stop that nurse!

487
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:13,320
The sun's going out, and you're
photographing a man and a dog. Why?

488
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:15,440
- Amy?
- Hi!

489
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:17,800
Oh, this is Rory, he's a.. friend.

490
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,600
- Boyfriend.
- Kind of boyfriend.

491
00:35:19,680 --> 00:35:22,320
Amy! Man and dog, why?

492
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:28,080
- Oh, my God, it's him.
- Just answer his question, please.

493
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:29,760
It's him, though. The Doctor.

494
00:35:29,840 --> 00:35:31,720
- The Raggedy Doctor.
- Yeah, he came back.

495
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:35,160
- But he was a story. He was a game.
- Man and dog - why? Tell me now.

496
00:35:35,240 --> 00:35:37,320
Sorry. Because he can't be there.

497
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:40,320
- Because he's in a hospital, in a coma.
- In a hospital, in a coma.

498
00:35:40,400 --> 00:35:42,040
Yeah.

499
00:35:44,000 --> 00:35:45,760
Knew it. Multi-form, you see?

500
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:48,600
Disguise itself as anything,
but it needs a live feed.

501
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:51,600
A psychic link with a living
but dormant mind.

502
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:54,400
(IT SNAPS AND SNARLS)

503
00:35:58,280 --> 00:36:00,560
Prisoner Zero.

504
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:03,120
- What, there's a Prisoner Zero too?
- Yes.

505
00:36:08,280 --> 00:36:11,480
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

506
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:18,160
See, that ship up there
is scanning this area

507
00:36:18,240 --> 00:36:20,600
for non-terrestrial technology.

508
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:26,520
And nothing says non-terrestrial
like a sonic screwdriver.

509
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:36,880
- (GLASS SMASHES, CAR ALARMS BLARE)
- Aargh!

510
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:41,360
- (SIREN WAILS)
- MAN: Hey, come back here!

511
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:45,360
Oi, come back here! Come back!

512
00:36:50,240 --> 00:36:53,240
I think someone's going to notice.
Don't you?

513
00:36:53,320 --> 00:36:55,120
(BARKING)

514
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:06,960
No, no, no, don't do that!

515
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:12,200
- Look, it's going.
- No, come back, he's here!

516
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:16,160
Come back! He's here,
Prisoner Zero is here.

517
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:21,520
Come back, he's here!
Prisoner Zero is...here.

518
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:22,640
Doctor!

519
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:25,640
The drain. It just sort of melted
and went down the drain.

520
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,840
- Well, of course it did.
- What do we do now?

521
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:31,400
It's hiding in human form.
We need to drive it into the open.

522
00:37:31,480 --> 00:37:34,760
No TARDIS, no screwdriver,
17 minutes.

523
00:37:34,840 --> 00:37:37,520
Come on, think. Think!

524
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:40,560
DR RAMSDEN: Barney? Barney...

525
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:44,520
Barney? Can you hear me, Barney?

526
00:37:46,320 --> 00:37:49,800
Barney? Barney?

527
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:02,640
So that thing,
that hid in my house for 12 years?

528
00:38:02,720 --> 00:38:04,920
Multi-forms can live for millennia.
12 years is a pit-stop.

529
00:38:05,040 --> 00:38:08,440
So how come you show up on the same day
that lot do, the same minute?

530
00:38:08,560 --> 00:38:11,600
They're looking for him, but followed me.
They saw me through the crack, got a fix.

531
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:13,400
They're only late cos I am.
Give me your phone.

532
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:16,480
- How can he be real? He was never real.
- Phone, now, gimme!

533
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:19,560
He was just a game, we were kids.
You made me dress up as him.

534
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:21,400
- These photos are all coma patients?
- Yeah.

535
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:22,920
No, they're all the multi-form.

536
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:25,200
Eight comas, eight disguises
for Prisoner Zero.

537
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:26,920
He had a dog.
There's a dog in a coma?

538
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:29,200
The coma patient dreams
he's walking a dog,

539
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:30,760
Prisoner Zero gets a dog. Laptop!

540
00:38:30,840 --> 00:38:32,360
Your friend, what was his name?

541
00:38:32,440 --> 00:38:34,400
- Not him, the good-looking one.
- Thanks.

542
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:35,600
- Jeff
h, thanks(!)

543
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:37,920
He had a laptop in his bag, a laptop.

544
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,800
Big bag, big laptop,
I need Jeff's laptop.

545
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:42,920
You two, get to the hospital,
get everyone out.

546
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:45,440
Clear the whole floor.
Phone me when you're done.

547
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:50,720
- Your car, come on.
- Um...but how can he be here?

548
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:52,720
How can the Doctor be here?

549
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:07,840
- Hello! Laptop, gimme!
- No, no, no, no, wait.

550
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:09,360
- It's fine.
- Hang on!

551
00:39:09,440 --> 00:39:11,160
Give it here.

552
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,880
Blimey! Get a girlfriend, Jeff.

553
00:39:16,640 --> 00:39:18,320
- Gran.
- What are you doing?

554
00:39:18,400 --> 00:39:20,640
The sun's gone wibbly,
so right now,

555
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:23,080
somewhere out there, there's going
to be a big video conference call.

556
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:27,480
All the experts in the world panicking
at once, and do you know what they need?

557
00:39:27,560 --> 00:39:30,280
Me. Ah, and here they all are.

558
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:35,480
All the big boys - NASA, Jodrell Bank,
Tokyo Space Centre, Patrick Moore.

559
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:37,400
- I like Patrick Moore.
- I'll get you his number,

560
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:38,880
but watch him, he's a devil.

561
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,000
- You can't just hack in on a call.
- Can't I?

562
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:44,440
Who are you? This is a secure call,
what are you doing?

563
00:39:44,560 --> 00:39:47,880
Hello, I know, you should switch me off.
But before you do, watch this.

564
00:39:47,960 --> 00:39:50,800
- It's here too, I'm getting it.
- Fermat's Theorem, the proof,

565
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,880
and I mean the real one,
never seen before.

566
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:56,200
Poor old Fermat, got killed in a duel
before he could write it down.

567
00:39:56,280 --> 00:39:58,320
My fault, I slept in.

568
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:01,800
Oh, and here's an oldie, but a goo die -
why electrons have mass.

569
00:40:01,880 --> 00:40:03,800
And a personal favourite of mine,

570
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:07,160
faster-than-light travel
with two diagrams and a joke.

571
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:10,320
Look at your screens.
Whoever I am, I'm a genius.

572
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:13,280
Look at the sun.
You need all the help you can get.

573
00:40:13,360 --> 00:40:16,400
Fellas, pay attention.

574
00:40:30,880 --> 00:40:33,320
AMERICAN MAN: Sir, what are you doing?

575
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:34,960
I'm writing a computer virus.

576
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:38,280
Very clever, super-fast,
and a tiny bit alive, but don't let on.

577
00:40:38,360 --> 00:40:41,040
Why am I writing it on a phone?
Never mind, you'll find out.

578
00:40:41,120 --> 00:40:43,880
OK, I'm sending this
to all your computers.

579
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:46,440
Get everyone who works for you
sending this everywhere.

580
00:40:46,520 --> 00:40:49,080
E-mail, text, Facebook, Bebo, Twitter,
radar dish -

581
00:40:49,160 --> 00:40:51,000
whatever you've got. Any questions?

582
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:53,800
- Who was your lady friend?
- Patrick, behave!

583
00:40:53,880 --> 00:40:56,800
- What does this virus do?
- It's a reset command, that's all.

584
00:40:56,880 --> 00:41:01,000
It resets counters, gets in the WiFi
and resets every counter it can find.

585
00:41:01,080 --> 00:41:04,120
Anything with a chip will default
at zero at exactly the same time.

586
00:41:04,200 --> 00:41:07,120
But, yeah, I could be lying.
Why should you trust me?

587
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:08,920
I'll let my best man explain.

588
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:16,640
Jeff...you're my best man.

589
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,760
You what?

590
00:41:19,320 --> 00:41:22,560
Listen to me. In ten minutes,
you're going to be a legend.

591
00:41:22,680 --> 00:41:26,360
In ten minutes, everyone is going to be
offering you any job you want.

592
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:28,680
But first, you have to be magnificent.

593
00:41:28,760 --> 00:41:32,760
You have to make them trust you
and get them working. This is it, Jeff.

594
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:34,080
Right here, right now.

595
00:41:34,160 --> 00:41:37,040
This is when you fly.

596
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,960
Today's the day you save the world.

597
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,960
- Why me?
- It's your bedroom.

598
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,840
Now go, go, go.

599
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:54,400
OK, guys,

600
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,960
let's do this.

601
00:41:57,680 --> 00:42:01,240
Oh, and delete
your internet history.

602
00:42:13,360 --> 00:42:16,200
Something's happened up there,
we can't get through.

603
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:19,360
Yes, but what's happened?

604
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,720
I don't know. No-one knows.
Phone him.

605
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,400
I'm phoning him.

606
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:26,160
Doctor? We're at the hospital,
but we can't get through.

607
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:27,840
Oh!

608
00:42:27,920 --> 00:42:30,120
- What did he say?
- Look in the mirror.

609
00:42:32,800 --> 00:42:35,000
Ha-ha! Uniform!

610
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:38,480
Are you on your way?

611
00:42:38,560 --> 00:42:40,000
You're going to need a car.

612
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:42,760
Don't worry.
I've commandeered a vehicle.

613
00:42:42,840 --> 00:42:45,520
(SIREN WAILS)

614
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:52,320
Oh, God!

615
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,160
- Officer.
- What happened?

616
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:02,000
There was a man. A man with a dog.

617
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:04,800
I think Dr Ramsden's dead.
And the nurses.

618
00:43:06,120 --> 00:43:07,880
(MOBILE RINGS)

619
00:43:09,120 --> 00:43:11,200
- Are you in?
- Yep.

620
00:43:11,280 --> 00:43:14,040
- But so's Prisoner Zero.
- You need to get out of there.

621
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:16,920
WOMAN'S VOICE: He was so angry.
He kept shouting. And that dog,

622
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:19,440
the size of that dog,
I swear it was rabid.

623
00:43:19,560 --> 00:43:22,360
WOMAN'S VOICE: And he just went mad,
attacking everyone.

624
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:26,600
Where did he go, did you see?
Has he gone? We hid in the ladies'.

625
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:30,480
Oh, I'm getting it wrong again, aren't I?
I'm always doing that.

626
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:32,440
So many mouths.

627
00:43:35,400 --> 00:43:38,440
- RORY: Oh, my God!
- (SNARLING)

628
00:43:38,520 --> 00:43:40,520
Amy? Amy, what's happening?

629
00:43:53,560 --> 00:43:56,040
(SIREN WAILS)

630
00:43:56,120 --> 00:43:57,520
Amy, talk to me!

631
00:43:57,600 --> 00:43:59,640
We're in the coma ward.
But it's here, it's getting in.

632
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:01,880
- Which window are you?
- What, sorry?

633
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:04,280
- Which window?
- First floor on the left,

634
00:44:04,360 --> 00:44:05,760
fourth from the end.

635
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:10,720
(SNARLING)

636
00:44:12,040 --> 00:44:14,600
Oh, dear. Little Amelia Pond.

637
00:44:15,720 --> 00:44:17,920
I've watched you grow up.

638
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:22,640
12 years, and you never even knew
I was there.

639
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:29,880
Little Amelia Pond,
waiting for her magic Doctor to return.

640
00:44:29,960 --> 00:44:32,960
But not this time, Amelia.

641
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:36,320
(MOBILE BEEPS)

642
00:44:36,400 --> 00:44:38,520
(SIREN WAILS)

643
00:44:48,720 --> 00:44:51,760
Right! Hello! Am I late?

644
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,920
No, three minutes to go.
So still time.

645
00:44:54,000 --> 00:44:56,520
Time for what...Time Lord?

646
00:44:59,640 --> 00:45:01,000
Take the disguise off.

647
00:45:01,080 --> 00:45:03,440
They'll find you in a heartbeat.
Nobody dies.

648
00:45:03,520 --> 00:45:06,600
The Atraxi will kill me this time.

649
00:45:06,680 --> 00:45:08,760
If I am to die,

650
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:10,720
let there be fire.

651
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:14,280
OK. You came to this world
by opening a crack in space and time.

652
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:18,520
- Do it again - just leave.
- I did not open the crack.

653
00:45:18,600 --> 00:45:20,560
Somebody did.

654
00:45:20,680 --> 00:45:26,720
The cracks in the skin of the universe -
don't you know where they came from?

655
00:45:28,280 --> 00:45:30,400
You don't, do you?

656
00:45:30,480 --> 00:45:33,560
GIRL'S VOICE: The Doctor
in the TARDIS doesn't know.

657
00:45:33,640 --> 00:45:35,920
(CHANTS) Doesn't know, doesn't know!

658
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:39,000
WOMAN'S VOICE:
The universe is cracked.

659
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:41,080
The Pandorica will open.

660
00:45:41,160 --> 00:45:44,120
Silence will fall.

661
00:45:46,480 --> 00:45:48,240
(CLICKING)

662
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:51,280
And we're off!

663
00:45:51,360 --> 00:45:52,920
Look at that.

664
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:58,080
Look at that!

665
00:46:01,000 --> 00:46:03,280
Yeah, I know,
just a clock, whatever.

666
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:06,480
But do you know
what's happening right now?

667
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:09,080
In one little bedroom,
my team are working.

668
00:46:09,160 --> 00:46:12,560
Jeff and the world.
And do you know what they're doing?

669
00:46:12,640 --> 00:46:16,360
They're spreading the word
all over the world, quantum fast.

670
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,720
The word is out.

671
00:46:23,960 --> 00:46:26,360
And do you know what the word is?

672
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:31,520
The word is zero.

673
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:34,160
Now, me, if I was up
in the sky in a battleship,

674
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:37,520
monitoring all Earth communications,
I'd take that as a hint.

675
00:46:37,600 --> 00:46:40,760
And if I had a whole battle fleet
surrounding the planet,

676
00:46:40,840 --> 00:46:44,960
I'd be able track a simple
old computer virus to its source

677
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:46,880
in, what, under a minute?

678
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:49,120
The source, by the way,

679
00:46:49,200 --> 00:46:50,840
is right here.

680
00:46:53,000 --> 00:46:56,320
Oh! And I think they just found us!

681
00:47:02,360 --> 00:47:04,480
The Atraxi are limited.

682
00:47:04,560 --> 00:47:08,160
While I'm in this form,
they'll still be unable to detect me.

683
00:47:08,240 --> 00:47:11,840
- They've tracked a phone, not me.
- Yeah,

684
00:47:11,920 --> 00:47:16,040
but this is the good bit.
I mean, this is my favourite bit.

685
00:47:16,120 --> 00:47:20,720
Do you know
what this phone is full of?

686
00:47:20,800 --> 00:47:22,640
Pictures of you.

687
00:47:22,720 --> 00:47:25,440
Every form you've learned to take,
right here.

688
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:29,240
Oh, and being uploaded about now.

689
00:47:29,320 --> 00:47:32,840
And the final score is -
no TARDIS, no screwdriver -

690
00:47:32,920 --> 00:47:35,280
two minutes to spare. Who da man?

691
00:47:39,360 --> 00:47:41,960
Oh, I'm never saying that again. Fine.

692
00:47:42,040 --> 00:47:44,240
Then I shall take a new form.

693
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:46,160
Oh, stop it, you know you can't.

694
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:49,280
Takes months to form
that kind of psychic link.

695
00:47:49,360 --> 00:47:51,920
And I've had years.

696
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:59,000
No! Amy?

697
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:01,960
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

698
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:03,800
You've got to hold on. Amy!

699
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:07,120
Don't sleep!
You've got to stay awake, please.

700
00:48:07,200 --> 00:48:08,240
Doctor?

701
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:17,320
Well, that's rubbish.
Who's that supposed to be?

702
00:48:17,400 --> 00:48:21,200
- It's you.
- Me? Is that what I look like?

703
00:48:21,280 --> 00:48:23,920
- You don't know?
- Busy day. Why me, though?

704
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:26,840
You're linked with her.
Why are you copying me?

705
00:48:26,920 --> 00:48:28,680
GIRL'S VOICE: I'm not.

706
00:48:31,400 --> 00:48:33,480
Poor Amy Pond.

707
00:48:33,560 --> 00:48:35,760
Still such a child inside.

708
00:48:35,840 --> 00:48:39,760
Dreaming of the magic Doctor
she knows will return to save her.

709
00:48:42,800 --> 00:48:45,400
What a disappointment you've been.

710
00:48:47,600 --> 00:48:50,120
No, she's dreaming about me
cos she can hear me.

711
00:48:53,440 --> 00:48:55,560
Amy, don't just hear me, listen.

712
00:48:55,640 --> 00:48:57,800
Remember the room, the room
in your house you couldn't see?

713
00:48:57,880 --> 00:49:00,800
Remember you went inside?
I tried to stop you, but you did.

714
00:49:05,840 --> 00:49:07,120
You went in the room.

715
00:49:09,640 --> 00:49:12,320
You went inside.

716
00:49:13,160 --> 00:49:14,880
Amy...

717
00:49:14,960 --> 00:49:17,920
dream about what you saw.

718
00:49:25,920 --> 00:49:28,840
No!

719
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:46,200
- Well done, Prisoner Zero.
- (ROARS)

720
00:49:47,400 --> 00:49:50,160
A perfect impersonation of yourself.

721
00:49:53,200 --> 00:49:54,840
Prisoner Zero is located.

722
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:57,880
Prisoner Zero is restrained.

723
00:50:00,640 --> 00:50:02,480
(HISSING) Silence, Doctor.

724
00:50:02,560 --> 00:50:04,840
Silence will fall.

725
00:50:08,080 --> 00:50:12,080
(WHOOSHING)

726
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:17,600
(BIRDSONG)

727
00:50:22,080 --> 00:50:24,680
The sun - it's back to normal, right?

728
00:50:24,760 --> 00:50:28,920
That's... That's good, yeah?
That means it's over.

729
00:50:31,000 --> 00:50:32,880
Amy?

730
00:50:32,960 --> 00:50:35,240
- Are you OK? Are you with us?
- What happened?

731
00:50:35,320 --> 00:50:37,360
- He did it. The Doctor did it.
- No, I didn't.

732
00:50:37,440 --> 00:50:40,240
- What are you doing?
- Tracking the signal back.

733
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:42,840
- Sorry...in advance.
- About what?

734
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:44,360
The bill.

735
00:50:44,440 --> 00:50:47,320
-Um...
- Oi, I didn't say you could go!

736
00:50:47,400 --> 00:50:50,120
Article 57
of the Shadow Proclamation.

737
00:50:50,200 --> 00:50:54,480
This is a fully established,
level 5 planet,

738
00:50:54,560 --> 00:50:57,560
and you were going to burn it? What?

739
00:50:57,640 --> 00:51:00,280
Did you think no-one was watching?

740
00:51:00,360 --> 00:51:02,360
You lot, back here, now!

741
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:05,800
OK.

742
00:51:05,880 --> 00:51:07,600
Now I've done it.

743
00:51:07,680 --> 00:51:09,480
Did he just bring them back?

744
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:13,880
Did he just save the world from aliens
and then bring all the aliens back again?

745
00:51:16,160 --> 00:51:18,800
- Where are you going?
- The roof.

746
00:51:18,880 --> 00:51:20,920
No, hang on.

747
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:29,760
- What's in here?
- I'm saving the world.

748
00:51:29,840 --> 00:51:31,800
I need a decent shirt.

749
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:33,960
To hell with the raggedy.

750
00:51:34,040 --> 00:51:36,240
Time to put on a show!

751
00:51:37,280 --> 00:51:40,400
You just summoned aliens back to Earth.

752
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:41,840
Actual aliens,

753
00:51:41,920 --> 00:51:43,240
deadly aliens,

754
00:51:43,320 --> 00:51:45,840
aliens of death,

755
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,120
and now you're taking your clothes off.

756
00:51:48,240 --> 00:51:52,080
- Amy, he's taking his clothes off.
- Turn your back if it embarrasses you.

757
00:51:52,160 --> 00:51:54,800
Are you stealing clothes now?

758
00:51:54,880 --> 00:51:58,520
Those clothes belong to people, you know.

759
00:52:02,200 --> 00:52:04,680
Are you not going to turn your back?

760
00:52:06,880 --> 00:52:07,920
Nope.

761
00:52:09,080 --> 00:52:11,240
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

762
00:52:12,880 --> 00:52:16,840
So this was a good idea, was it(?)
They were leaving.

763
00:52:16,920 --> 00:52:20,200
Leaving is good.
Never coming back is better.

764
00:52:20,280 --> 00:52:23,440
Come on, then!

765
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:26,920
The Doctor will see you now.

766
00:52:33,280 --> 00:52:35,640
(WHIRRING)

767
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:41,800
You are not of this world.

768
00:52:41,880 --> 00:52:45,160
No, but I've put a lot of work into it.

769
00:52:45,240 --> 00:52:46,880
Hmm...

770
00:52:46,960 --> 00:52:48,640
I don't know.

771
00:52:48,720 --> 00:52:50,440
What do you think?

772
00:52:50,520 --> 00:52:52,040
Is this world important?

773
00:52:52,120 --> 00:52:54,720
Important?
What's that mean, "important"?

774
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:57,720
Six billion people live here -
is that important?

775
00:52:57,800 --> 00:53:01,080
Here's a better question.
Is this world a threat to the Atraxi?

776
00:53:01,160 --> 00:53:04,440
Well, come on.
You're monitoring the whole planet.

777
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:07,240
Is this world a threat?

778
00:53:12,120 --> 00:53:13,480
No.

779
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:16,600
Are the peoples of this world
guilty of any crime

780
00:53:16,680 --> 00:53:19,840
by the laws of the Atraxi?

781
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:23,040
No.

782
00:53:23,120 --> 00:53:24,280
OK.

783
00:53:25,840 --> 00:53:27,400
One more. Just one.

784
00:53:28,960 --> 00:53:31,800
Is this world protected?

785
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:38,880
Because you're not the first lot to come
here. Oh, there have been so many!

786
00:53:40,720 --> 00:53:42,560
And what you've got to ask is...

787
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:45,560
...what happened to them?

788
00:53:56,920 --> 00:53:58,200
Hello.

789
00:53:58,280 --> 00:53:59,760
I'm the Doctor.

790
00:54:04,560 --> 00:54:06,800
Basically...

791
00:54:08,680 --> 00:54:10,560
---Fun.

792
00:54:10,640 --> 00:54:13,760
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

793
00:54:39,560 --> 00:54:41,040
Is that it?

794
00:54:41,120 --> 00:54:45,400
Is that them gone for good?
Who were they?

795
00:55:05,160 --> 00:55:06,960
OK!

796
00:55:07,040 --> 00:55:09,880
What have you got for me this time?

797
00:55:17,280 --> 00:55:18,760
Look at you!

798
00:55:21,840 --> 00:55:24,400
Oh, you sexy thing!

799
00:55:25,960 --> 00:55:27,440
Look at you!

800
00:55:31,520 --> 00:55:34,440
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

801
00:56:04,240 --> 00:56:06,720
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

802
00:56:28,400 --> 00:56:30,640
Sorry about running off earlier.

803
00:56:30,720 --> 00:56:33,560
Brand-new TARDIS - bit exciting.

804
00:56:33,640 --> 00:56:36,600
Just had a quick hop to the moon
and back to run her in.

805
00:56:37,680 --> 00:56:39,360
She's ready for the big stuff now.

806
00:56:39,440 --> 00:56:41,200
(OWL HOOTS)

807
00:56:41,280 --> 00:56:44,120
It's you. You came back.

808
00:56:44,200 --> 00:56:46,960
Course I came back.
I always come back.

809
00:56:47,040 --> 00:56:50,360
- Something wrong with that?
- And you kept the clothes.

810
00:56:50,440 --> 00:56:53,240
Well, I just saved the world,
the whole planet,

811
00:56:53,320 --> 00:56:55,520
for about the millionth time,
no charge. Yeah, shoot me!

812
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:58,480
- I kept the clothes.
- Including the bow tie.

813
00:56:58,560 --> 00:57:01,680
- Yeah, it's cool. Bow ties are cool.
- Are you from another planet?

814
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:03,240
- Yeah.
- OK.

815
00:57:03,320 --> 00:57:04,680
So what do you think?

816
00:57:04,720 --> 00:57:06,680
- Of what?
- Other planets. Want to check some out?

817
00:57:06,760 --> 00:57:09,120
- What does that mean?
- It means...

818
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:12,200
Well, it means...come with me.

819
00:57:12,280 --> 00:57:13,960
Where?

820
00:57:14,040 --> 00:57:16,560
Wherever you like.

821
00:57:16,640 --> 00:57:18,080
(OWL HOOTS)

822
00:57:18,160 --> 00:57:21,640
All that stuff - the hospital,
the spaceships, Prisoner Zero...

823
00:57:21,720 --> 00:57:25,120
Oh, don't worry. That's just
the beginning. There's loads more.

824
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:29,520
Yeah, but those things, those...
amazing things, all that stuff...

825
00:57:31,720 --> 00:57:34,600
- ...that was two years ago!
- Oh-oh!

826
00:57:34,680 --> 00:57:36,280
- Oops.
- Yeah.

827
00:57:36,360 --> 00:57:38,000
- So that's...
- 14 years!

828
00:57:38,080 --> 00:57:40,000
14 years since fish custard.

829
00:57:40,080 --> 00:57:43,360
Amy Pond, the girl who waited,
you've waited long enough.

830
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:48,440
When I was a kid, you said there was
a swimming pool and a library,

831
00:57:48,520 --> 00:57:50,920
- and the pool was /777 the library.
- Yeah.

832
00:57:51,000 --> 00:57:52,840
Not sure where it is now. So...coming?

833
00:57:52,920 --> 00:57:54,360
No.

834
00:57:54,440 --> 00:57:57,440
- You wanted to come 14 years ago.
- I grew up.

835
00:57:57,520 --> 00:57:59,200
Don't worry.

836
00:57:59,280 --> 00:58:00,760
I'll soon fix that.

837
00:58:39,040 --> 00:58:40,600
Well?

838
00:58:40,680 --> 00:58:44,040
Anything you want to say?
Any passing remarks?

839
00:58:44,120 --> 00:58:46,440
I've heard them all.

840
00:58:55,160 --> 00:58:56,680
I'm in my nightie.

841
00:58:56,760 --> 00:59:00,040
Oh, don't worry.
Plenty of clothes in the wardrobe.

842
00:59:00,120 --> 00:59:02,200
And possibly a swimming pool.

843
00:59:03,200 --> 00:59:06,360
So...all of time and space,

844
00:59:06,440 --> 00:59:09,520
everything that ever happened
or ever will...

845
00:59:09,600 --> 00:59:11,200
Where do you want to start?

846
00:59:13,760 --> 00:59:15,880
You are so sure that I'm coming.

847
00:59:15,960 --> 00:59:18,040
- Yeah, I am.
- Why?

848
00:59:18,120 --> 00:59:20,440
Cos you're the Scottish girl
in the English village,

849
00:59:20,520 --> 00:59:22,880
- and I know how that feels.
- Oh, do you?

850
00:59:22,960 --> 00:59:25,720
All these years living here,
most of your life...

851
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:27,880
and you've still got that accent.
Yeah, you're coming.

852
00:59:27,960 --> 00:59:30,000
(BELL RINGS)

853
00:59:30,080 --> 00:59:33,240
- Can I be back by tomorrow morning?
- It's a time machine.

854
00:59:33,320 --> 00:59:35,600
You can be back five minutes ago.
Why, what's tomorrow?

855
00:59:35,680 --> 00:59:38,720
Nothing. Nothing. Just...you know, stuff.

856
00:59:41,480 --> 00:59:44,960
All right, then.
Back in time for "stuff".

857
00:59:46,680 --> 00:59:49,720
Oh! A new one!

858
00:59:49,800 --> 00:59:51,640
Lovely.

859
00:59:52,760 --> 00:59:54,320
(WHISPERS) Thanks, dear!

860
00:59:57,440 --> 00:59:58,960
(BEEPING)

861
01:00:06,520 --> 01:00:09,440
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

862
01:00:11,800 --> 01:00:12,880
Why me?

863
01:00:12,960 --> 01:00:14,880
- Why not?
- Seriously. You are asking me

864
01:00:14,960 --> 01:00:16,880
to run away with you
in the middle of the night.

865
01:00:16,960 --> 01:00:18,480
It's a fair question. Why me?

866
01:00:18,600 --> 01:00:22,000
- I don't know. Fun. Do I need a reason? -
People always have a reason.

867
01:00:22,080 --> 01:00:23,480
- Do I look like people?
- Yes.

868
01:00:23,560 --> 01:00:25,720
Been knocking around
on my own for a while.

869
01:00:25,800 --> 01:00:28,720
My choice. But I've started talking
to myself. It's giving me earache.

870
01:00:28,800 --> 01:00:33,800
- You're lonely. That's it? Just that?
- Just that.

871
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:35,080
Promise.

872
01:00:35,160 --> 01:00:37,440
(RUMBLING)

873
01:00:37,520 --> 01:00:39,760
OK.

874
01:00:39,840 --> 01:00:42,760
(RUMBLING)

875
01:00:44,440 --> 01:00:45,800
So, are you OK, then?

876
01:00:45,880 --> 01:00:49,360
Cos this place, sometimes
it can make people feel a bit...

877
01:00:49,440 --> 01:00:51,520
- you know...
- I'm fine.

878
01:00:51,640 --> 01:00:54,800
It's just...there's a whole world in here,
just like you said.

879
01:00:54,880 --> 01:00:57,800
It's all true. I thought...
Well, I started to think that maybe

880
01:00:57,920 --> 01:01:00,240
- you were just like a madman with a box.
- Amy Pond,

881
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:04,560
there's something you'd better understand,
cos one day your life may depend on it.

882
01:01:04,640 --> 01:01:07,600
I am definitely a madman with a box.

883
01:01:09,320 --> 01:01:11,920
Ha-ha! Yeah.

884
01:01:12,000 --> 01:01:13,800
(SHE LAUGHS)

885
01:01:13,880 --> 01:01:16,920
Goodbye, Leadworth.
Hello, everything!

886
01:01:17,000 --> 01:01:18,880
WWhoo!

887
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:22,200
(METALLIC THRUMMING)

888
01:01:22,280 --> 01:01:24,080
Ha-ha!

